%20grads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-kelsey-hightower-self-taught-developer-kubernetes-cloud-computing-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKelsey%20Hightower%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20retired%20from%20Google%20in%202023%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20current%20job%20market%20is%20vastly%20different%20from%20the%20one%20he%20entered%20decades%20ago%2C%20but%20young%20people%20still%20have%20more%20control%20over%20their%20careers%20than%20they%20may%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20is%20definitely%20a%20very%20convenient%20reason%20to%20look%20at%20what%20you're%20currently%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hightower%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-workplace-more-productive-less-social-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI's%20effect%20on%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20industry%20is%20undergoing%20a%20%26quot%3Brecalibration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20is%20that%20for%20the%20last%2020%20to%2030%20years%2C%20we've%20taken%20millions%20of%20super%20bright%20people%20who%20would've%20been%20good%20at%20anything%2C%20and%20we%20pushed%20them%20all%20into%20tech%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20three%20pieces%20of%20advice%20Hightower%20has%20for%20new%20graduates%20and%20early-career%20workers%2C%20especially%20those%20looking%20to%20break%20into%20the%20tech%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d88098b5-171f-47e7-bfa4-9c23189778d3%5C%22%3ETreat%20extracurriculars%20like%20a%20job%20requirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHightower%20said%20that%20the%20new%20%26quot%3Bharsh%20reality%26quot%3B%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-college-still-worth-it-tech-execs-kids-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egrades%20and%20diplomas%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20no%20longer%20enough%20to%20stand%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20your%20work%20has%20been%20at%20school%2C%20you%20do%20projects%20for%20school%2C%20maybe%20you%20get%20a%20GPA%2C%20maybe%20you%20get%20a%20diploma%20from%20that%2C%20but%20no%20one%20knows%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20provide%20anything%20special%20or%20if%20you're%20just%20another%20person%20graduating%2C%26quot%3B%20Hightower%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20show%20your%20work%20in%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20now%20going%20into%20the%20workforce%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20put%20together%20a%20strong%20set%20of%20extracurricular%20activities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHightower%20said%20prospective%20graduates%20should%20think%20about%20workforce%20preparation%20the%20same%20way%20they%20once%20approached%20college%20admissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20open%20source%20projects%2C%20real-world%20things%20that%20you've%20actually%20built%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20internships%2C%20but%20things%20that%20people%20can%20really%20point%20to%20to%20say%2C%20oh%2C%20this%20was%20a%20meaningful%20contribution%2C%20whether%20it's%20to%20a%20company%20or%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b3870a1-51c5-4f29-955d-00a270d28b32%5C%22%3EInvest%20in%20real-world%20relationships%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReferrals%20remain%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20pathways%20into%20coveted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-job-search-white-collar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etech%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Hightower%20said%2C%20but%20many%20younger%20workers%20came%20of%20age%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20have%20built%20far%20more%20online%20connections%20than%20in-person%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20network%20really%20matters%2C%26quot%3B%20Hightower%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20being%20in%20the%20physical%20world%20next%20to%20other%20people%20that%20are%20doing%20this%20work%20or%20going%20through%20the%20same%20challenges%20as%20you%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20very%20different%20than%20trying%20to%20do%20that%20online.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20remembers%20attending%20programming-language%20meetups%20and%20technology%20gatherings%20when%20he%20was%20younger%2C%20but%20sees%20fewer%20people%20investing%20in%20face-to-face%20professional%20relationships%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20on%20Reddit%2C%20they're%20on%20social%20media%2C%20they're%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20them%20posting%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20really%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20building%20those%20real-world%20connections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22045a9b60-79ea-46dc-af5a-798c3c874128%5C%22%3EDon't%20become%20a%20'senior%20engineer%20and%20a%20junior%20human'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHightower%20said%20that%20new%20graduates%20shouldn't%20lose%20hope%20in%20the%20face%20of%20AI%20and%20should%20focus%20on%20their%20human%20qualities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20student%20really%20has%20to%20start%20thinking%20about%20what%20we%20traditionally%20call%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmo-gawdat-google-most-valuable-skill-in-the-ai-era-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoft%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BLike%20understanding%20people%2C%20being%20creative%2C%20artistic%2C%20having%20a%20big%20vision%2C%20having%20experienced%20the%20world%2C%20and%20all%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fethan-mollick-ai-expert-wharton-taste-skills-ai-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecreative%20elements%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20typically%20don't%20get%20measured%20in%20the%20interview%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20only%20things%20that%20AI%20can't%20do%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20no%20experience.%20It%20has%20no%20empathy%20for%20the%20human%20condition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20many%20workplaces%20have%20created%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Ba%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkelsey-hightower-google-ai-replacing-enigeers-only-coding-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esenior%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20junior%20human%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20around%2020%25%20of%20workers%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20more%20robotic%20and%20are%20%26quot%3Breduced%20down%26quot%3B%20to%20what%20a%20computer%20could%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20promise%20you%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20not%20performing%20to%20the%20best%20of%20their%20ability%2C%20and%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20it's%20not%20their%20fault%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20driven%20the%20motivation%20out%20of%20you%20to%20the%20point%20where%20you're%20almost%20just%20doing%20what%20a%20robot%20would%20do%3A%20open%20this%20ticket%2C%20assign%20this%20task%2C%20write%20this%20code%2C%20check%20it%20in%2C%20rinse%20and%20repeat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStart%20making%20that%20list%20today.%20What%20can%20I%20bring%20to%20the%20table%20that%20this%20AI%20model%20cannot%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkelsey-hightower-google-distinguished-engineer-tips-for-new-graduates-ai-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780909621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a22f423b4fb977f35984d1a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkelsey-hightower-google-distinguished-engineer-tips-for-new-graduates-ai-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kelsey%20Hightower%20offers%20advices%20for%20young%20people%20and%20fresh%20grads%20who%20are%20entering%20an%20uncertain%20job%20market%2C%20as%20AI%20dampens%20hiring.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22katherineli%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%2