lication%20space.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BSuper-app%20talk%20is%20mostly%20noise%20that's%20going%20to%20get%20resolved%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20VC%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20I%20had%20a%20noble%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20my%20job%2C%20I%20have%20to%20remember%20a%20lot%20of%20AI%20companies%2C%20so%20I%20thought%20I'd%20draw%20up%20a%20competition%20map%20for%20my%20desk.%20I'd%20divvy%20a%20sheet%20of%20paper%20into%20columns%20and%20list%20major%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecompanies%20based%20on%20which%20part%20of%20the%20AI%20supply%20chain%20they're%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20the%20labs%20%E2%80%94%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20Google%20DeepMind%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%94%20that%20are%20making%20models%20and%20chatbots.%20There%20were%20the%20AI%20coding%20platforms%20%E2%80%94%20Cursor%2C%20Cognition%2C%20and%20Replit%20among%20them%20%E2%80%94%20that%20build%20coding%20assistants%20powered%20by%20those%20models.%20Then%2C%20there%20were%20startups%20building%20hyper-specific%20applications%3A%20agents%20that%20live%20in%20your%20email%2C%20help%20you%20execute%20a%20marketing%20strategy%2C%20or%20automate%20boring%20tasks%20like%20payroll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20the%20map%20would%20get%20messy%2C%20fast%2C%20because%20AI%20companies%20are%20ruthlessly%20invading%20each%20other's%20turf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEver-increasing%20valuations%20mean%20companies%20need%20to%20find%20new%20sources%20of%20revenue.%20Becoming%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-full-stack-dream-microsoft-nightmare-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efull-stack%20AI%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20especially%20important%20for%20revenue%20when%20models%20are%20commoditizing%20fast%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-submits-s-1-joins-ipo-race-with-openai-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebig-ticket%20IPOs%20loom%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Here's%20how%20the%20landscape%20is%20evolving%2C%20way%20too%20fast%20for%20my%20paper%20map%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fff9898f-3a8b-4997-bb4e-9995b4ce2614%5C%22%3EMore%20vibe%20coders%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20that%20start%20with%20a%20narrow%20AI%20capability%20%E2%80%94%20frontier%20models%2C%20AI%20agents%2C%20vibe-coding%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20are%20quickly%20expanding%20into%20one%20or%20more%20of%20those%20other%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Anthropic%20and%20OpenAI%20launched%20Claude%20Code%20and%20Codex%2C%20AI%20coding%20platforms%20that%20rival%20Cursor%20and%20Cognition.%20Now%2C%20per%20user%20screenshots%20on%20X%20%E2%80%94%20Anthropic%20won't%20confirm%20it%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20may%20be%20working%20on%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Ean%20app%20builder%20for%20non-techies%2C%20putting%20it%20squarely%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-raising-billions-vibe-coding-boom-cursor-lovable-replit-emergent-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompetition%20with%20vibe-coding%20stars%20%3C%2Fa%3ELovable%2C%20Replit%2C%20and%20Emergent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoftBank%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-startup-emergent-launching-agent-rival-openclaw-nanobot-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELightspeed-backed%20Emergent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20one%2C%20says%20it%20saw%20Anthropic%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20surprise.%20We've%20been%20anticipating%20this%20for%20a%20while%20and%20sort%20of%20internally%20thinking%20and%20preparing%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20CEO%20Mukund%20Jha%20told%20me%20in%20an%20April%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic's%20entry%20into%20the%20vibe-coding%20market%20is%20not%20game%20over%20for%20the%20year-old%20startup%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCoding%20is%20relatively%20like%2020%25-30%25%20of%20the%20work.%20The%20hard%20work%20is%20actually%20taking%20the%20application%20to%20the%20last%20mile%2C%26quot%3B%20Jha%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20building%20secure%20and%20production-grade%20apps%2C%20especially%20for%20non-technical%20users%2C%20is%20a%20tough%20problem%2C%20one%20that%20might%20not%20be%20solved%20by%20companies%20that%20may%20be%20%26quot%3Bspread%20thin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ded7081a-10bf-4e4d-a245-4314462a8218%5C%22%3EClaw%20rush%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20AI%20turf%20war%2C%20OpenAI%20is%20making%20agentic%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20the%20lab%20announced%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenclaw-peter-steinberger-ai-token-bill-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehiring%20Peter%20Steinberger%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20creator%20of%20OpenClaw%2C%20an%20AI%20assistant%20builder%20that%20skyrocketed%20in%20popularity%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20added%20OpenAI%20to%20the%20list%20of%20companies%20building%20in%20the%20agentic%20space%2C%20such%20as%20former%20Meta%20tech%20chief%20Bret%20Taylor's%20Sierra%20and%20Salesforce's%20AI%20agent%20platform%20Agentforce.%20Now%2C%20Codex%20has%20evolved%20from%20a%20coding%20assistant%20to%20a%20virtual%20AI%20agent%20that%20can%20parse%20and%20reply%20to%20emails%2C%20manage%20files%2C%20and%20schedule%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmaller%20players%20are%20excited%20about%20this%20space%2C%20too.%20Last%20month%2C%20Emergent%2C%20which%20started%20as%20a%20vibe-coding%20platform%2C%20expanded%20into%20the%20personal%20agent%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20examples%20of%20the%20growing%20overlap%20include%20Anthropic%20entering%20the%20design%20market%20and%20graphic%20design%20giant%20Canva%20entering%20the%20broader%20generative%20AI%20and%20productivity%20suite%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b2edb503-d8ca-40a0-b694-170c15fd5a6c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Google%20wanted%20to%20touch%20everything'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20sounds%20like%20you've%20heard%20this%20story%20before%2C%20you%20have.%20But%20instead%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20Lovable%2C%20the%20characters%20were%20Google%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichiel%20Kotting%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20European%20venture%20firm%20Northzone%2C%20said%20that%20there%20was%20a%20time%20when%20the%20FAANG%20companies%20were%20dipping%20their%20fingers%20in%20all%20the%20pies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKotting%2C%20who%20cofounded%20e-commerce%20platform%20Shopping.com%2C%20said%20that%20Google%20used%20to%20be%20a%20big%20source%20of%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%2025%20years%20ago%20when%20I%20was%20building%20my%20first%20company%2C%20Google%20wanted%20to%20touch%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20April.%20%26quot%3BFor%20us%20at%20Shopping.com%2C%20we%20had%20Google%20launch%20Froogle%2C%20which%20was%20exactly%20what%20we%20were%20doing.%20And%20we're%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20we're%20dead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20it%20was%20a%20side%20project.%20They%20made%20so%20much%20money%20on%20their%20core%20business%2C%20so%20how%20hard%20would%20they%20go%20after%20it%3F%20Well%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20they%20didn't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETom%20Sheridan%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20early%20Lovable%20investor%20RTP%20Global%2C%20agreed%20that%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20app%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20one%20app%20to%20rule%20them%20all%20%E2%80%94%20is%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-summit-prediction-markets-super-apps-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESuper%20app%20talk%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20mostly%20noise%20that's%20going%20to%20get%20resolved%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-ipo-racing-to-go-public-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIPO%20calendar%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Right%20now%20we're%20seeing%20the%20foundational%20model%20players%20in%20the%20throes%20of%20a%20game%20of%20P%26amp%3BL%20chicken%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20these%20companies%20go%20public%2C%20cash%20burn%20stops%20being%20free%20and%20shipping%20into%20categories%20where%20you're%20good-but-not-best%20stops%20making%20sense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BGoogle%20Graveyard%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20unofficial%20online%20list%2C%20tracks%20305%20projects%20sunsetted%20by%20the%20search%20giant%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%2C%20too%2C%20is%20famous%20for%20%26quot%3BSherlocking%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20introducing%20a%20new%20feature%20that%20makes%20a%20third-party%20tool%20irrelevant%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20don't%20always%20stick%20around.%20In%202023%2C%20Apple%20launched%20Pay%20Later%2C%20a%20rival%20to%20Klarna%20and%20Affirm.%20It%20discontinued%20it%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKotting%20said%20that%20we%20may%20see%20the%20same%20happen%20with%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%2C%20companies%20feared%20by%20founders%20for%20the%20day%20they%20might%20ship%20an%20application%20startups%20have%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebeen%20working%20on%20for%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20more%20worthwhile%20for%20Anthropic%20to%20continue%20building%20better%20models%20so%20it%20can%20charge%20more%20for%20its%20core%20service%2C%20he%20said.%20But%20if%20Chinese%20players%20or%20other%20labs%20become%20equally%20good%20and%20models%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepseek-researcher-chen-deli-china-jobs-ai-risk-tech-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eturn%20into%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20commodity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Anthropic%20may%20go%20harder%20on%20these%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20getting%20%26quot%3BSherlocked%2C%26quot%3B%20startups%20face%20another%20big%20risk%3A%20dependency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStartups%20are%20building%20billion-dollar%20businesses%20on%20top%20of%20APIs%20controlled%20by%20companies%20that%20may%20eventually%20compete%20with%20them.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-xai-explored-collaborating-with-mistral-cursor-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECursor%20depends%20on%20Anthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%20models%20to%20power%20its%20features%2C%20but%20the%20two%20also%20compete%20as%20coding%20assistant%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224414c2cf-eb99-4ead-9fef-8be4b7279d8e%5C%22%3EShort-term%20win%20for%20customers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20players%20doling%20out%20more%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efreebies%20is%20a%20win%20for%20individual%20builders%20and%20small%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20said%20Sheridan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFoundation%20model%20companies%20can%20ship%20a%20passable%20version%20of%20almost%20anything%2C%20but%20if%20the%20bundled%20tool%20isn't%20as%20good%20as%20the%20specialist%20tool%20I%20already%20use%2C%20I%20revert%20back%20in%20a%20single%20session%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20VC%20said.%20%26quot%3BProduct%20sprawl%20in%20search%20of%20retention%20bumps%20risks%20worsening%20UX%20and%20users%20know%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20labs%20like%20OpenAI%20and%20Google%20sprawling%20in%20every%20direction%20also%20means%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-google-search-ai-overview-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20like%20Reddit%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20LinkedIn%2C%20which%20host%20tons%20of%20data%2C%20shutting%20out%20scrapers.%20That's%20bad%20news%20for%20small%20startups%20like%20sales%20tech%20tools%20or%20meeting%20summarizers%20kept%20from%20the%20data%20they%20want%20to%20build%20their%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20bring%20an%20opportunity%20for%20founders%20who%20know%20what%20users%20want%20out%20of%20their%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday's%20crop%20of%20foundational%20models%20can%20see%20meeting%20transcripts%20shared%20for%20summarization%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20know%20which%20folders%20they%20should%20be%20filed%20under%2C%20what%20a%20team%20actually%20cares%20about%20or%20the%20required%20follow-up%20actions%2C%26quot%3B%20Sheridan%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20gap%20startups%20can%20build%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20is%20also%20ripe%20for%20consolidation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'd%20expect%20one%20of%20the%20major%20consumer%20AI%20breakouts%20to%20get%20acquired%20within%20the%20next%2024%20months%2C%20most%20likely%20by%20Google%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BGoogle%20has%20the%20consumer%20ads%20business%20to%20absorb%20the%20cost%20and%20is%20structurally%20the%20most%20desperate%20for%20consumer%20AI%20talent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESheridan%20said%20that%20the%20first%20company%20to%20be%20bought%20gets%20the%20best%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20the%20last%20consumer%20AI%20play%20standing%20when%20each%20major%20buyer%20probably%20only%20takes%20one%20shot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-is-building-everything-openai-anthropic-lovable-cursor-canva-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780876801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a23655a2ab5f9757add9d11%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-is-building-everything-openai-anthropic-lovable-cursor-canva-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20are%20ruthlessly%20invading%20each%20other's%20turf.%20Ever-increasing%20valuations%20mean%20companies%20need%20to%20find%20new%20sources%20of%20revenue.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sgoel%40insider.com%20(Shubhangi%20Goel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tsunami%20alert%20after%207.8-mag